text: Trou aux Cerfs (also known as Murr's Volcano) is a dormant volcano in Curepipe, Mauritius. It is high and has a well-defined cone and crater. The crater has been alternately described as 300 and 350 meters in diameter, and is 80 meters deep. ==Sources== Category:Volcanoes of Africa Category:Geography of Mauritius
title: Trou aux Cerfs
